<paragraph pageNumber="793">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="793">Note:</emphasis>
Fawcett &amp; Rendle (
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="793">Fl. Jamaica</emphasis>
5: 300. 1926) noted the presence of material in LINN but did not refer to it as the type, despite the attribution of Nicolson &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="793">Regnum Veg.</emphasis>
119: 217. 1988) of a typification to these authors. Keay (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="793">Kew Bull.</emphasis>
8: 123. 1953) designated material in 
<specimenReference collectionCode="BM-SL">
Herb. Sloane (
<collectionCode>BM-SL</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
, but as it was neither seen by Linnaeus, nor was it even the basis for a Sloane illustration, it is not original material for the name.
</paragraph>
